External knowledge:
- Cumulative revenue is calculated as the sum of revenues for each genre or producer over time, assuming the release dates represent the order in which revenues are added;
- The production stages ('pre-production', 'production', 'post-production') are sequential and hierarchical, with each movie going through these stages in this order;
- The genre and producer names are used to group movies for cumulative revenue calculations.
